Ecosystem & Tooling Selection
  Before writing code, we need to map the Python libraries to their C++ equivalents and set up the build system.


   * Build System: CMake (Industry standard for C++).
   * Computer Vision: OpenCV C++ (cv::VideoCapture, cv::Mat).
   * Inference (YOLOv11): TensorRT (NVIDIA) or ONNXRuntime. We will need to export your .pt models to .onnx or .engine formats.
   * Object Tracking: C++ implementation of ByteTrack (readily available on GitHub).
   * Messaging (RabbitMQ): amqp-cpp or SimpleAmqpClient.
   * Web Streaming (MJPEG): cpp-httplib (lightweight header-only HTTP server).
   * Motor Control (Moteus): Moteus provides a C++ API (moteus-cpp or direct SocketCAN wrappers).
   * Hardware/Serial Comm: Boost.Asio or a lightweight library like serialib for Arduino (Trigger, Sensors, Zoom).
   * Configuration/State: nlohmann/json for JSON parsing (for runtime_state.json, fov_data.json, etc.).


Phase 1: Ecosystem & Tooling Selection (DONE)
   * Build System: CMake setup.
   * Libraries: Integrated OpenCV, Threads, and established nlohmann/json usage.
   * Structure: Created include/ and src/ directories.


  Phase 2: Foundation & State Management (DONE)
   * Globals: Migrated Globals.py to Globals.h.
   * OpModes: Migrated Python enums to C++ enum class.
   * Shared State: Implemented a thread-safe SharedState using std::atomic and std::shared_mutex to replace Python's multiprocessing.Manager.
   * Data Manager: Implemented DataManager to load JSON fov/pid/depth data and a MathUtils helper for linear interpolation.


  Phase 3: Hardware & Messaging Interfaces (ONGOING)
   * Serial Wrappers: Created SerialPort, TriggerController (Solenoid/Laser), and ZoomController (VISCA).
   * Pending:
       * Motor Integration: Moving from mock MotorController to real moteus-cpp SocketCAN implementation.
       * Messaging: Implementing RabbitMQ interface (likely using amqp-cpp or a proxy).


  Phase 4: Vision & Inference Pipeline (ONGOING)
   * Capture: Implemented CameraReader using high-performance C++ threads.
   * Streaming: Implemented a high-speed MJPEGStreamer using cpp-httplib.
   * Pending:
       * TensorRT Inference: Replacing the YoloEngine stub with actual TensorRT engine loading and GPU pre-processing.
       * Tracking: Implementing the C++ ByteTrack logic.


  Phase 5: The Control Loop (ONGOING)
   * PID Logic: Implemented PIDController class with command calculation.
   * System Orchestration: Created RakshakSystem to manage the lifecycle of all threads.
   * Pending:
       * Target locking logic, firing timers, and mode-switching refinements within the RakshakSystem control thread.


  Phase 6: Final Assembly & Validation (PENDING)
   * Creating the final high-performance executable.
   * Hardware-in-the-loop testing (CAN bus, Serial latency).
   * Performance benchmarking (FPS vs. Latency).